.TH man 8 "April 2017" "1.0" "vscnprintf man page"
.SH NAME
vscnprintf \- Kernel string APIs
.SH SYNOPSIS
vscnprintf - continue
.SH DESCRIPTION
formats a string and place it in a buffer
#include <string.h>
The return value is the number of characters which have been written into the buf not including the trailing '\0'. If size is == 0 the function returns 0.
.SH OPTIONS
Takes arguments as destination buffer, size of the buffer (including the trailing
space), the format of the string to use, arguments of the format string.
.SH SEE ALSO
list*
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Tapasweni Pathak (tapaswenipathak@gmail.com)
